256
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:47,145
And so now, I turn into godly stardust,

257
00:19:47,229 --> 00:19:48,981
and say farewell.

258
00:19:49,690 --> 00:19:50,691
Oh, look.

259
00:19:51,316 --> 00:19:53,193
Do you see? It's happening.

260
00:19:54,152 --> 00:19:55,612
I'm disappearing.

261
00:20:00,117 --> 00:20:01,702
No!

262
00:20:01,785 --> 00:20:02,786
Father!

263
00:20:04,997 --> 00:20:06,415
But wait! Brother!

264
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:11,044
An ominous portal
hath appeared behind us.

265
00:20:11,628 --> 00:20:12,754
Transform!

266
00:20:22,598 --> 00:20:25,350
I am Hela, Goddess of Death.

267
00:20:25,434 --> 00:20:27,561
Now, I return to Asgard

268
00:20:27,644 --> 00:20:30,480
to stake my claim
as the rightful heir to the throne,

269
00:20:30,564 --> 00:20:32,399
and no one will stop me!

270
00:20:32,482 --> 00:20:33,442
Join me or die!

271
00:20:33,525 --> 00:20:34,860
We will never join you, witch!

272
00:20:34,943 --> 00:20:35,903
Mjolnir!

273
00:20:40,824 --> 00:20:42,075
Impossible!

274
00:20:43,619 --> 00:20:45,454
I broke your hammer!

275
00:20:45,537 --> 00:20:47,080
Time to die!

276
00:20:47,247 --> 00:20:48,540
Bifrost!

277
00:21:00,385 --> 00:21:02,846
You can almost feel the power

278
00:21:03,013 --> 00:21:05,766
of these magnificent
and immovable stones.

279
00:21:06,308 --> 00:21:08,685
Okay. Let's head back to the village

280
00:21:08,852 --> 00:21:11,855
where we can drink
some real Asgardian mead.

281
00:21:11,939 --> 00:21:13,482
Come on.

282
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:50,060
God of Disaster,

283
00:21:51,228 --> 00:21:52,437
we thank you.

284
00:21:52,521 --> 00:21:54,481
We feared we would be at war forever

285
00:21:54,564 --> 00:21:56,358
without the protection of our gods,

286
00:21:56,525 --> 00:21:59,486
but now, peace shall reign.

287
00:22:00,028 --> 00:22:03,448
In return for your service,
please accept these gifts.

288
00:22:04,783 --> 00:22:07,327
As is tradition,
the protectors of our world

289
00:22:07,411 --> 00:22:09,496
are bestowed with great beasts.

290
00:22:12,082 --> 00:22:13,125
Giant goats!

291
00:22:13,208 --> 00:22:15,210
Oh, look at those! They are wonderful.

292
00:22:15,293 --> 00:22:18,171
Korg, look at that.
Those things are beautiful.

293
00:22:18,255 --> 00:22:20,716
King Yakan, thank you so much.

294
00:22:20,799 --> 00:22:22,634
Listen, um, about the temple...

295
00:22:22,718 --> 00:22:23,844
I don't wanna talk about the temple.

296
00:22:23,927 --> 00:22:25,012
I know, but if we were to talk about it,

297
00:22:25,095 --> 00:22:26,346
- I think it's important...
- It's making me sad.

298
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:27,431
...to life and material objects...

299
00:22:27,514 --> 00:22:28,807
- And mad.
- Okay, I'll stop talking.

300
00:22:28,890 --> 00:22:30,600
Don't forget the goats.

301
00:22:30,684 --> 00:22:33,061
Which you accepted,
and now must take with you.

302
00:22:33,145 --> 00:22:34,354
No backsies.

303
00:22:35,105 --> 00:22:38,233
- Aw. They are beautiful.
- Yes, they are beautiful.

304
00:22:39,401 --> 00:22:40,944
They also scream quite a lot.

305
00:22:41,028 --> 00:22:41,987
They'll be fine.

306
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:44,072
I am Groot.

307
00:22:44,156 --> 00:22:45,198
We need to find the damn remote

308
00:22:45,282 --> 00:22:46,950
so we can download the distress signal!

309
00:22:47,034 --> 00:22:49,077
Retrace your steps.
Where did you put the remote?

310
00:22:49,161 --> 00:22:50,495
One of your goats probably ate it!

311
00:22:50,579 --> 00:22:52,330
Goats didn't eat the remote.
Don't be ridiculous.

312
00:22:52,414 --> 00:22:53,832
Well, I ain't digging through
their crap.

313
00:22:53,915 --> 00:22:55,625
I love them!

314
00:22:55,709 --> 00:22:56,710
They should live with us forever!

315
00:22:56,793 --> 00:22:57,919
Found the remote!

316
00:22:58,086 --> 00:22:59,129
I'm putting them down.

317
00:22:59,212 --> 00:23:00,297
- Me too.
- Is it working or not?

318
00:23:00,380 --> 00:23:01,673
No, it's not workin'. It's not charged.

319
00:23:01,757 --> 00:23:02,758
Well, maybe you need to find a charger...

320
00:23:02,841 --> 00:23:03,884
Get out of my way!

321
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:05,177
Hey, hey! Whoa, whoa, whoa! Whoa, whoa!

322
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:07,012
Whew.

323
00:23:07,095 --> 00:23:08,889
- Korg, you okay?
- Yeah, bro. All good.

324
00:23:08,972 --> 00:23:10,182
All right. Everybody, just relax.

325
00:23:10,265 --> 00:23:11,433
The goats are gonna be fine.

326
00:23:11,516 --> 00:23:13,185
If not, we can just use them for meat...

327
00:23:15,103 --> 00:23:16,730
...ting people. Meeting people.

328
00:23:16,813 --> 00:23:18,231
They're a great conversation starter.

329
00:23:18,315 --> 00:23:20,776
And I've been told you can summon them
with a special whistle

330
00:23:20,859 --> 00:23:22,444
that goes something like this...

331
00:23:22,527 --> 00:23:24,321
No, that's not it.
No, that's not it.

332
00:23:24,404 --> 00:23:25,822
No, that's not it. You have a go.

333
00:23:25,906 --> 00:23:27,324
No, that's not it.

334
00:23:27,407 --> 00:23:29,284
- Oh, hey, guys.
- Kraglin!

335
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:30,410
No, that's not it.

336
00:23:30,494 --> 00:23:32,746
- You been here this whole time?
- Yeah, you said to stay with the ship.

337
00:23:32,829 --> 00:23:35,165
This is Glenda. We're married.

338
00:23:35,248 --> 00:23:37,334
I am Groot.

339
00:23:37,417 --> 00:23:38,418
What did we tell you

340
00:23:38,502 --> 00:23:40,003
about jumpin' into new relationships?

341
00:23:40,170 --> 00:23:41,421
That I shouldn't be doing that.

342
00:23:41,505 --> 00:23:42,589
Yeah, you can't get married

343
00:23:42,672 --> 00:23:44,132
on every single planet we land on.

344
00:23:44,216 --> 00:23:45,801
I am Groot.

345
00:23:45,884 --> 00:23:47,803
Finally!

346
00:23:47,969 --> 00:23:49,763
All right, here we go. Distress calls.

347
00:23:50,347 --> 00:23:53,100
<i>Please help us!</i>
<i>The God Butcher has found us!</i>

348
00:23:53,183 --> 00:23:54,434
God Butcher?

349
00:23:54,518 --> 00:23:56,186
<i>He left them</i>
<i>hanging as a warning.</i>

350
00:23:56,269 --> 00:23:58,146
Look at all of these gods, murdered.

351
00:23:58,230 --> 00:24:00,107
<i>Our greatest champions,</i>

352
00:24:00,190 --> 00:24:02,025
<i>now laid to waste.</i>

353
00:24:02,109 --> 00:24:03,235
The horror.

354
00:24:03,318 --> 00:24:04,778
Who could have done something like this?

355
00:24:05,904 --> 00:24:07,030
<i>Thor, where are you?</i>

356
00:24:07,114 --> 00:24:08,698
Wait, wait, wait.
What was that? Go back.

357
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,201
Play that one.

358
00:24:12,786 --> 00:24:14,287
<i>- Thor, where are you?</i>
- Sif?

359
00:24:14,371 --> 00:24:15,622
<i>We need you here.</i>

360
00:24:16,373 --> 00:24:18,333
My friend is in danger.
We must go at once.

361
00:24:18,416 --> 00:24:19,793
Start the ship, my friends.

362
00:24:19,876 --> 00:24:21,878
I don't know, maybe we should split up.

363
00:24:21,962 --> 00:24:22,963
So many people to save,

364
00:24:23,046 --> 00:24:25,048
I mean, look at all of these distress...

365
00:24:25,132 --> 00:24:26,633
...calls.

366
00:24:30,011 --> 00:24:31,012
Thor.

367
00:24:31,179 --> 00:24:32,514
You gonna be okay?

368
00:24:32,681 --> 00:24:34,141
I admire your commitment to each other.

369
00:24:34,224 --> 00:24:35,350
It's a beautiful thing.

370
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:37,227
Alas, it's something I'll never have.

371
00:24:37,394 --> 00:24:38,770
Buddy, if I may...

372
00:24:39,354 --> 00:24:40,397
You may.

373
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:43,150
After thousands of years of living,

374
00:24:43,233 --> 00:24:44,442
you don't seem to know
who the hell you are.

375
00:24:45,443 --> 00:24:46,903
I've been lost before.

376
00:24:47,904 --> 00:24:49,614
But then I found meaning, I found love.

377
00:24:50,866 --> 00:24:51,950
And yeah, it got taken from me,

378
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:53,160
and god, that hurts.

379
00:24:55,036 --> 00:24:57,706
But that shitty feeling
is better than feeling empty.

380
00:24:59,249 --> 00:25:00,250
My hope for you is that

381
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:02,878
one day, you will find something

382
00:25:03,336 --> 00:25:05,505
to make you feel this shitty.

383
00:25:05,589 --> 00:25:08,508
I have loved before. It didn't work out.

384
00:25:08,592 --> 00:25:10,677
They either die a grismal death

385
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:12,429
or they dump you
with a handwritten letter.

386
00:25:12,512 --> 00:25:13,513
I don't know which is worse,

387
00:25:13,597 --> 00:25:15,765
but it's why I keep everyone
at arm's length.

388
00:25:18,685 --> 00:25:19,686
You've grown too attached.

389
00:25:19,769 --> 00:25:20,937
Damn it, I knew this would happen.

390
00:25:21,021 --> 00:25:22,898
You must go. I'll find Sif.

391
00:25:23,648 --> 00:25:24,858
You answer the other calls.

392
00:25:24,941 --> 00:25:26,318
The galaxy needs its Guardians.

393
00:25:26,401 --> 00:25:27,402
Cool, yeah. We were just leaving...

394
00:25:27,485 --> 00:25:28,904
Shh. I know it hurts.

395
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:30,739
But it's better this way.
You have to trust me.

396
00:25:31,698 --> 00:25:33,366
To ease the pain, why don't you, uh,

397
00:25:34,367 --> 00:25:36,870
take this ship here
as a parting farewell gift?

398
00:25:37,579 --> 00:25:38,955
Oh, you're giving me my ship?

399
00:25:39,039 --> 00:25:40,332
Yes, she's yours.

400
00:25:40,415 --> 00:25:43,210
May you make as many memories
with her as I have.

401
00:25:43,376 --> 00:25:44,878
She's a temperamental old lass.

402
00:25:45,045 --> 00:25:47,422
Will serve you well in a tight pickle.

403
00:25:47,505 --> 00:25:48,715
- I'll start the ship.
- Thank you.

404
00:25:48,798 --> 00:25:50,091
Goodbye, old friend.

405
00:25:51,718 --> 00:25:53,011
A human handshake

406
00:25:53,094 --> 00:25:54,971
to the Asgardian shake.

407
00:25:55,138 --> 00:25:57,599
Into the snake that you cannot trust.

408
00:25:58,767 --> 00:25:59,893
You're really dragging this out.

409
00:25:59,976 --> 00:26:02,812
And finish with the classic
Asgardian high one.

410
00:26:06,775 --> 00:26:07,943
Let's go.

411
00:26:08,026 --> 00:26:09,110
Take care of my crew.

412
00:26:09,194 --> 00:26:10,278
This is gonna be hard for them.

413
00:26:10,362 --> 00:26:11,571
Hurry up!

414
00:26:11,655 --> 00:26:12,739
Not her.

415
00:26:12,822 --> 00:26:14,157
Remember what I told you.

416
00:26:15,116 --> 00:26:16,576
You ever feel lost,

417
00:26:17,369 --> 00:26:19,663
just look into the eyes
of the people that you love.

418
00:26:19,746 --> 00:26:22,123
They'll tell you exactly who you are.

419
00:26:26,503 --> 00:26:27,462
All right. Bye.

420
00:26:31,174 --> 00:26:33,468
For what it's worth,
let's cling to the good memories.

421
00:26:33,551 --> 00:26:35,303
We Asgardians say,

422
00:26:35,387 --> 00:26:37,973
"May you travel with the speed
of Odin's ravens.

423
00:26:38,431 --> 00:26:39,599
"I'll see you in Valhalla

424
00:26:39,683 --> 00:26:41,518
"where we shall drink mead and..."

425
00:26:43,228 --> 00:26:45,689
- They're gone.
- Alone again. Just me and you.

426
00:26:45,772 --> 00:26:47,023
Stormbreaker!

427
00:26:47,941 --> 00:26:49,985
Watch out, you frickin' crazy axe!

428
00:26:53,613 --> 00:26:54,823
So what do we do now, bro?

429
00:26:54,906 --> 00:26:56,324
Let's go get Sif!

430
00:27:11,881 --> 00:27:13,717
Who or what is that?

431
00:27:13,883 --> 00:27:17,012
Falligar, God of the Falligarians.

432
00:27:17,512 --> 00:27:19,514
One of the nicest gods you'll ever meet.

433
00:27:21,099 --> 00:27:22,225
Oh, no.

434
00:27:31,026 --> 00:27:32,986
Sif, it's me, Thor.

435
00:27:33,570 --> 00:27:34,529
Odinson?

436
00:27:34,612 --> 00:27:36,114
You're missing an arm.

437
00:27:36,197 --> 00:27:37,449
I'm gonna get you home.

438
00:27:37,532 --> 00:27:39,659
No! Leave me here.

439
00:27:39,743 --> 00:27:41,703
I want to die a warrior's death.

440
00:27:41,870 --> 00:27:43,913
On the battlefield. In battle.

441
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,958
And then I can claim my place
in Valhalla.

442
00:27:47,542 --> 00:27:49,502
Oh, I hate to break it to you,

443
00:27:49,586 --> 00:27:51,087
but for a warrior to get into Valhalla,

444
00:27:51,171 --> 00:27:52,547
you have to die in the battle.

445
00:27:53,256 --> 00:27:55,258
- You survived.
- Oh, shit.

446
00:27:55,884 --> 00:27:57,635
Maybe your arm is in Valhalla.

447
00:27:59,429 --> 00:28:00,555
What happened here?

448
00:28:00,638 --> 00:28:02,640
I've been hunting a madman.

449
00:28:02,807 --> 00:28:04,851
I followed him here, but it was a trap.

450
00:28:05,018 --> 00:28:06,019
Who is this madman?

451
00:28:06,603 --> 00:28:08,813
The God Butcher is coming.

452
00:28:08,897 --> 00:28:11,316
He seeks the extinction of the gods.

453
00:28:11,399 --> 00:28:13,360
Asgard is next.

454
00:30:03,761 --> 00:30:04,888
Look, it's Thor!

455
00:30:04,971 --> 00:30:06,931
- Thor!
- Take Sif to the infirmary.

456
00:30:07,182 --> 00:30:08,183
Hey!

457
00:30:08,266 --> 00:30:09,476
Who'd you piss off now?

458
00:30:09,559 --> 00:30:11,060
This is not my fault.
I've never even seen these things,

459
00:30:11,144 --> 00:30:12,145
whatever the hell they are.

460
00:30:12,228 --> 00:30:13,438
Welcome back.

461
00:30:38,838 --> 00:30:39,964
Who's the new guy?

462
00:30:40,548 --> 00:30:42,842
That guy? You're gonna love that guy.

463
00:30:57,232 --> 00:30:59,609
Mjol... Mjolnir! Mjolnir!

464
00:30:59,692 --> 00:31:00,818
It's me, Thor.

465
00:31:00,902 --> 00:31:02,153
Have you seen my hammer?

466
00:31:02,237 --> 00:31:03,780
Mjolnir, here, boy.

467
00:31:05,698 --> 00:31:07,283
Mjolnir?

468
00:31:11,538 --> 00:31:12,622
Mjolnir.

469
00:31:17,377 --> 00:31:19,837
You're back!

470
00:31:23,550 --> 00:31:24,384
Mjolnir!

471
00:31:52,036 --> 00:31:53,413
Excuse me.

472
00:31:53,496 --> 00:31:55,248
Hello. That's my hammer
you've got there.

473
00:31:56,916 --> 00:31:58,084
And that's my look.

474
00:32:05,883 --> 00:32:06,884
Hey!

475
00:32:09,220 --> 00:32:10,346
Enough tomfoolery.

476
00:32:10,430 --> 00:32:12,682
Why don't you take off
that mask and reveal yourself?

477
00:32:12,765 --> 00:32:13,850
Come on.

478
00:32:15,768 --> 00:32:16,769
Hey.

479
00:32:17,395 --> 00:32:18,813
Jane?

480
00:32:24,152 --> 00:32:27,155
<i>Let me tell you</i>
<i>the legend of Thor and Jane.</i>

481
00:32:28,906 --> 00:32:32,994
<i>He was a God of Thunder</i>
<i>and she, a woman of science.</i>

482
00:32:34,162 --> 00:32:36,581
<i>And although they were</i>
<i>from different worlds,</i>

483
00:32:38,374 --> 00:32:40,460
<i>somehow, it just made sense.</i>

484
00:32:40,543 --> 00:32:41,377
Whoo! Ha-ha!

485
00:32:41,461 --> 00:32:42,879
<i>And together they embarked</i>

486
00:32:42,962 --> 00:32:44,881
<i>on a journey of love.</i>

487
00:32:50,553 --> 00:32:52,889
<i>Thor taught Jane the way of the warrior...</i>

488
00:32:55,308 --> 00:32:58,061
<i>And Jane taught Thor</i>
<i>the way of the people.</i>

489
00:32:59,354 --> 00:33:00,938
<i>And as time passed,</i>

490
00:33:01,022 --> 00:33:03,650
<i>their love grew deeper and deeper.</i>

491
00:33:06,778 --> 00:33:08,780
She's incredible, isn't she, Mjolnir?

492
00:33:11,407 --> 00:33:14,744
I need you to promise me
you'll always protect her.

493
00:33:16,454 --> 00:33:18,373
I love you too, buddy.

494
00:33:19,957 --> 00:33:23,544
<i>And love that deep</i>
<i>has a way of becoming magical.</i>

495
00:33:27,256 --> 00:33:29,759
<i>Thor set his sights toward a future</i>

496
00:33:29,842 --> 00:33:31,969
<i>and all it might hold.</i>

497
00:33:35,181 --> 00:33:37,850
<i>But the more he pondered</i>
<i>a life with Jane,</i>

498
00:33:37,934 --> 00:33:39,977
<i>the more he feared losing that life.</i>

499
00:33:40,061 --> 00:33:42,814
<i>And although</i>
<i>Jane didn't want to admit it,</i>

500
00:33:42,980 --> 00:33:45,316
<i>she was scared of loss as well.</i>

501
00:33:48,778 --> 00:33:51,030
<i>And so, they built walls between them.</i>

502
00:33:51,948 --> 00:33:53,991
<i>Thor got busy saving humanity.</i>

503
00:33:54,701 --> 00:33:55,785
Heimdall!

504
00:33:57,161 --> 00:33:59,831
<i>And Jane got busy doing the same.</i>

505
00:33:59,914 --> 00:34:01,708
<i>Real busy.</i>

506
00:34:01,791 --> 00:34:04,752
<i>And eventually, the space</i>
<i>between them grew and grew</i>

507
00:34:04,836 --> 00:34:06,921
<i>until it became too wide to bear.</i>

508
00:34:12,885 --> 00:34:14,345
<i>Something had to give.</i>

509
00:34:14,429 --> 00:34:17,974
I have to stay up all night
to go through this data. Okay?

510
00:34:18,057 --> 00:34:19,183
And I have to stay up all night

511
00:34:19,267 --> 00:34:21,436
- and clean all of this up.
- There's two plates!

512
00:34:21,519 --> 00:34:22,520
It's two plates and two forks!

513
00:34:26,858 --> 00:34:28,901
<i>And then, one night, it did give.</i>

514
00:34:30,528 --> 00:34:32,155
<i>Jane wrote a note.</i>

515
00:34:33,406 --> 00:34:35,408
<i>And Thor read that note.</i>

516
00:34:37,201 --> 00:34:39,829
<i>And their legend suddenly became myth.</i>

517
00:34:41,414 --> 00:34:43,249
<i>Or so they thought.</i>

518
00:34:45,835 --> 00:34:47,837
You okay?

519
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:50,882
Yeah...
it's a little, uh, hot in...

520
00:34:50,965 --> 00:34:53,009
Startin' to feel...

521
00:34:53,259 --> 00:34:56,053
It's claustrophobic with the helmet.

522
00:35:00,308 --> 00:35:01,309
How?

523
00:35:01,392 --> 00:35:02,810
Uh...

524
00:35:03,394 --> 00:35:05,730
Can we talk about this later?

525
00:35:06,272 --> 00:35:07,356
Yeah, sure.

526
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,775
Great seeing you.

527
00:35:10,401 --> 00:35:11,527
What?

528
00:35:17,909 --> 00:35:20,161
<i>Kill all the gods.</i>

529
00:35:58,616 --> 00:36:00,618
Hey. Is that the Necrosword?

530
00:36:00,785 --> 00:36:03,037
That's cool. I've only ever
read about it in stories.

531
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:06,123
Then you know this is going to hurt.

532
00:36:06,207 --> 00:36:07,917
Pain.

533
00:36:08,084 --> 00:36:10,461
What is pain but a construct
invented by the weak?

534
00:36:10,545 --> 00:36:11,838
Okay, that's very sharp!

535
00:36:21,180 --> 00:36:22,139
Ready?

536
00:36:23,015 --> 00:36:26,060
Don't touch my things.

537
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:54,881
Yeah, you better run, you coward.

538
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:16,402
The children.
They're taking the children!

539
00:37:16,485 --> 00:37:18,154
Mommy!

540
00:37:20,364 --> 00:37:21,407
Mom!

541
00:37:45,181 --> 00:37:47,642
Shadow monsters. Disgusting.

542
00:37:51,354 --> 00:37:53,564
Flew around the world twice. Nothing.

543
00:37:53,648 --> 00:37:56,901
- Cowards must have run away.
- We'll find them.

544
00:37:59,570 --> 00:38:01,530
- Quite a reunion, huh?
- Eh, you're telling me.

545
00:38:01,697 --> 00:38:03,532
What's it been? Like, three, four years?

546
00:38:03,824 --> 00:38:05,952
Eight years, seven months, and six days.

547
00:38:06,035 --> 00:38:07,370
I haven't forgotten

548
00:38:07,495 --> 00:38:08,704
the last time I saw you,

549
00:38:08,788 --> 00:38:10,539
or didn't see you, because you left.

550
00:38:10,623 --> 00:38:12,416
It's kind of an oversimplification

551
00:38:12,500 --> 00:38:13,584
to say that I left.

552
00:38:13,668 --> 00:38:15,920
Ah, no, you left. You did.

553
00:38:16,087 --> 00:38:17,922
You wrote me a beautiful
handwritten letter.

554
00:38:18,089 --> 00:38:20,049
I should know, I was there.

555
00:38:20,132 --> 00:38:21,300
- You weren't there...
- I was.

556
00:38:21,384 --> 00:38:22,760
...actually, hence the note.

557
00:38:24,387 --> 00:38:26,222
And if you weren't
there to see me leave,

558
00:38:26,305 --> 00:38:28,057
then maybe it was you that left.

559
00:38:28,933 --> 00:38:30,768
- Fair point. Hmm.
- Uh...

560
00:38:30,851 --> 00:38:32,311
Not that it matters.

561
00:38:32,395 --> 00:38:33,562
Like, who's keeping track, right?

562
00:38:33,646 --> 00:38:35,106
No, yeah.

563
00:38:35,189 --> 00:38:37,608
I suppose we both left
and both got left.

564
00:38:37,692 --> 00:38:38,818
Now you're leaving again.

565
00:38:40,945 --> 00:38:42,154
Miek, we need detailed accounts

566
00:38:42,238 --> 00:38:43,322
from all the witnesses.

567
00:38:43,406 --> 00:38:44,490
Darryl, get me all the names

568
00:38:44,573 --> 00:38:45,616
of the children who have been lost.

569
00:38:46,283 --> 00:38:47,702
Your Majesty,
my daughter has been taken,

570
00:38:47,785 --> 00:38:48,786
and I don't know where she is.

571
00:38:48,869 --> 00:38:50,246
And she'll be found.

572
00:38:50,329 --> 00:38:51,789
Guys, they're bleeding.

573
00:38:51,872 --> 00:38:53,290
Get them to the infirmary. Now!

574
00:38:53,374 --> 00:38:54,375
Darryl!

575
00:38:54,542 --> 00:38:56,460
Majesty, should we start working

576
00:38:56,544 --> 00:38:58,337
on a performance of this entire debacle?

577
00:38:58,504 --> 00:39:00,089
The people need entertainment.

578
00:39:00,172 --> 00:39:01,841
Particularly now, in times of crisis.

579
00:39:01,924 --> 00:39:03,509
Particularly.

580
00:39:05,511 --> 00:39:06,762
I did not hear a, "No."

581
00:39:07,221 --> 00:39:08,431
Nor did I.

582
00:39:08,597 --> 00:39:09,724
- Asgard. Night.
- Yes!

583
00:39:09,890 --> 00:39:11,100
We open on some sleeping children.

584
00:39:15,396 --> 00:39:17,690
So, that's the ex-girlfriend, is it?

585
00:39:17,773 --> 00:39:19,150
The old ex-girlfriend.

586
00:39:19,316 --> 00:39:20,359
Jodie Foster.

587
00:39:20,526 --> 00:39:21,569
Jane Foster.

588
00:39:21,652 --> 00:39:22,862
The one that got away.

589
00:39:22,945 --> 00:39:24,613
The one that got away.

590
00:39:24,697 --> 00:39:25,740
That means escaped.

591
00:39:25,823 --> 00:39:27,491
Yeah. Yeah... Yeah.

592
00:39:27,950 --> 00:39:29,785
Must be hard for you
to see your ex-girlfriend

593
00:39:29,869 --> 00:39:31,454
and your ex-hammer hangin' out,

594
00:39:31,537 --> 00:39:32,913
and getting on so well.

595
00:39:37,209 --> 00:39:38,461
What you up to, bro?

596
00:39:39,086 --> 00:39:40,463
Come on.

597
00:39:41,005 --> 00:39:42,256
Come to daddy.

598
00:39:42,339 --> 00:39:45,259
Come on. Mjolnir.

599
00:39:46,927 --> 00:39:49,638
Hey! There you are.

600
00:39:49,722 --> 00:39:50,765
Hey.

601
00:39:50,848 --> 00:39:51,891
Do you know
what I think we should do?

602
00:39:51,974 --> 00:39:53,684
- I was just calling you.
- Start an army!

603
00:39:53,768 --> 00:39:55,686
With what? Half our soldiers are dead!

604
00:39:55,770 --> 00:39:57,354
Half our soldiers are always dead!

605
00:39:57,438 --> 00:39:59,482
- Where are the children?
- Everyone, please go home.

606
00:39:59,565 --> 00:40:00,566
I promise you we'll have news soon.

607
00:40:00,649 --> 00:40:02,068
Someone needs to tell us what happened.

608
00:40:02,151 --> 00:40:03,736
We shall find them.

609
00:40:05,738 --> 00:40:07,073
- I just don't understand.
- You know what?

610
00:40:07,156 --> 00:40:08,449
This is all our fault.

611
00:40:08,532 --> 00:40:09,742
Stop it!

612
00:40:09,825 --> 00:40:10,910
Asgard!

613
00:40:19,710 --> 00:40:22,797
My friends, we must not quarrel.

614
00:40:23,756 --> 00:40:26,550
In times like this, we need
to unite, come together.

615
00:40:26,634 --> 00:40:28,761
I see what's happening here.

616
00:40:29,428 --> 00:40:31,639
You're afraid. Hmm?

617
00:40:32,264 --> 00:40:33,307
Scared.

618
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:35,643
Afraid.

619
00:40:35,726 --> 00:40:36,936
Anxious.

620
00:40:38,813 --> 00:40:39,814
If we are to find the children,

621
00:40:39,897 --> 00:40:43,025
we must first look within ourselves.

622
00:40:43,109 --> 00:40:44,902
I'm sorry. Miek, it's very hard

623
00:40:44,985 --> 00:40:47,446
to give a rousing speech
with the noise.

624
00:40:47,530 --> 00:40:49,073
- What are you doing?
- She's taking minutes.

625
00:40:49,156 --> 00:40:50,491
Oh, precious minutes we don't have.

626
00:40:50,574 --> 00:40:52,576
You want the kids back?

627
00:40:53,702 --> 00:40:55,329
I'll be back in a minute.

628
00:40:56,247 --> 00:40:57,581
You can write that down, Miek.

629
00:41:00,417 --> 00:41:01,252
No!

630
00:41:10,261 --> 00:41:12,012
Stormbreaker, what are you doing?

631
00:41:12,096 --> 00:41:13,597
Is this about Mjolnir?

632
00:41:13,681 --> 00:41:15,182
Everyone, out!

633
00:41:17,101 --> 00:41:18,936
Didn't find them.

634
00:41:19,019 --> 00:41:20,146
Oh, bae, your cape's on fire.

635
00:41:20,229 --> 00:41:21,272
It's fine. It'll grow back.

636
00:41:21,355 --> 00:41:22,773
I'm invoicing you for this.

637
00:41:22,857 --> 00:41:23,858
Listen.

638
00:41:23,941 --> 00:41:25,025
What do we know about this guy?

639
00:41:25,109 --> 00:41:26,485
He travels through shadows.

640
00:41:26,569 --> 00:41:28,070
And he creates monsters with them.

641
00:41:28,154 --> 00:41:29,655
Absolutely freaky monsters.

642
00:41:29,738 --> 00:41:31,824
He also wields the Necrosword.
How do I know that?

643
00:41:31,907 --> 00:41:33,367
Because he almost speared me
in the face with it.

644
00:41:33,450 --> 00:41:34,368
What's a Necrosword?

645
00:41:34,451 --> 00:41:35,870
It's an ancient weapon
that's been passed

646
00:41:35,953 --> 00:41:37,454
through hands since the dawn of time.

647
00:41:37,538 --> 00:41:39,790
It has the ability to slay gods,

648
00:41:39,874 --> 00:41:41,417
but it slowly corrupts and kills

649
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:43,002
whoever wields it, which means...

650
00:41:43,085 --> 00:41:44,587
Oh, so, it infected him.

651
00:41:44,670 --> 00:41:46,380
It's infecting him. Yes. It must be.

652
00:41:46,463 --> 00:41:48,966
So basically,
we're up against a cursed,

653
00:41:49,049 --> 00:41:50,801
shadow-zombie kidnapper.

654
00:41:51,177 --> 00:41:52,678
Awesome. When do we leave?

655
00:41:52,761 --> 00:41:54,138
Thor.

656
00:41:54,221 --> 00:41:55,723
Can you see me?

657
00:41:55,806 --> 00:41:57,057
Uh, floating head alert.

658
00:41:57,141 --> 00:41:58,976
It's Astrid. Heimdall's son.

659
00:41:59,059 --> 00:42:00,853
Astrid, are you okay?

660
00:42:00,936 --> 00:42:02,938
I no longer go by the name Astrid.

661
00:42:03,105 --> 00:42:05,065
I'm now known as Axl.

662
00:42:05,232 --> 00:42:07,443
He's a singer from a popular band
I heard on Earth.

663
00:42:07,526 --> 00:42:08,777
- G N' R.
- Astrid,

664
00:42:08,861 --> 00:42:10,863
your father gave you
a very tough Viking name

665
00:42:10,946 --> 00:42:12,531
and I intend to honour his wishes.

666
00:42:12,615 --> 00:42:13,699
- Axl.
- Astrid.

667
00:42:13,782 --> 00:42:14,992
- I said Axl.
- Astrid.

668
00:42:15,075 --> 00:42:17,286
- Axl!
- It's asshole. Now listen to him!

669
00:42:17,369 --> 00:42:19,955
All right, fine, Axl. Where are you?

670
00:42:20,122 --> 00:42:23,375
I'm not sure. I don't know
how to use my magic eyes yet.

671
00:42:23,459 --> 00:42:24,877
Your father taught me
and I'm gonna teach you.

672
00:42:24,960 --> 00:42:27,463
I need you to focus
and hold out your hand.

673
00:42:27,546 --> 00:42:30,090
Okay, good. Now focus.

674
00:42:30,257 --> 00:42:31,383
Close your eyes.

675
00:42:35,888 --> 00:42:38,390
Thor!

676
00:42:40,351 --> 00:42:41,769
Hey, how's it going, kids?

677
00:42:41,852 --> 00:42:43,687
"How's it going"? Look where we are.

678
00:42:43,854 --> 00:42:45,731
We're in a cage made of spikes.

679
00:42:46,398 --> 00:42:48,067
Yes, right. Not good. Yeah.

680
00:42:48,234 --> 00:42:49,318
Are you gonna do something?

681
00:42:49,401 --> 00:42:51,070
Yes. Yes, I am, but just not right now.

682
00:42:51,153 --> 00:42:53,155
I'm the vision ghost. Look.

683
00:42:54,573 --> 00:42:56,200
- See?
- What will happen to us?

684
00:42:56,283 --> 00:42:57,826
Who can tell?

685
00:42:57,910 --> 00:42:59,954
I mean, this is a very,
very bad situation.

686
00:43:00,120 --> 00:43:02,539
You know, the good news
is you're Asgardians.

687
00:43:02,706 --> 00:43:04,833
So, if you die,
you'll end up in Valhalla.

688
00:43:04,917 --> 00:43:06,085
Oh, my God. Go away.

689
00:43:06,252 --> 00:43:07,962
Wait, wait. Listen.

690
00:43:09,505 --> 00:43:10,881
Okay. It's all right, children.

691
00:43:10,965 --> 00:43:12,383
Don't cry. Don't cry. It's okay.

692
00:43:12,549 --> 00:43:13,884
Listen, I've got a plan, okay?

693
00:43:13,968 --> 00:43:15,970
I'm putting together
a really, really good team.

694
00:43:16,053 --> 00:43:19,640
We've got, um, Uncle Korg,
uh, King Valkyrie,

695
00:43:19,723 --> 00:43:21,850
um, my ex-girlfriend, Jane,

696
00:43:21,934 --> 00:43:24,144
which is a whole other story
I won't bore you with, okay?

697
00:43:24,228 --> 00:43:26,522
But it is a top-notch team,

698
00:43:26,605 --> 00:43:28,399
and we're gonna have you home
before you know it.

699
00:43:28,482 --> 00:43:29,733
Yeah.

700
00:43:37,116 --> 00:43:38,158
I know where you are.

701
00:43:41,370 --> 00:43:42,538
I'm gonna get you out of here.

702
00:43:42,621 --> 00:43:43,831
I'm scared.

703
00:43:43,914 --> 00:43:46,125
We all are.

704
00:43:46,208 --> 00:43:48,294
Thor! Thor! Save us.

705
00:43:52,006 --> 00:43:53,299
Get me out of here. You take care, okay?

706
00:43:53,382 --> 00:43:55,175
Take care. I'll see you soon. All right?

707
00:43:55,259 --> 00:43:56,510
Axl, get me out of here!

708
00:43:58,053 --> 00:43:59,096
They're in the Shadow Realm.

709
00:43:59,179 --> 00:44:00,264
How do you know?

710
00:44:00,431 --> 00:44:02,975
The heavy atmosphere there
has a darkness like no other.

711
00:44:03,142 --> 00:44:05,102
It's as if colour fears to tread.
It's unmistakable.

712
00:44:05,936 --> 00:44:07,604
Well then, if it's colour we need,

713
00:44:08,063 --> 00:44:09,565
let's bring the rainbow.

714
00:44:11,567 --> 00:44:13,444
"Bring the rainbow"?
Is that a catchphrase or something?

715
00:44:13,610 --> 00:44:15,154
She's only been a Thor for a minute.

716
00:44:15,237 --> 00:44:16,655
I mean, saving lives,
she's quite good at.

717
00:44:16,739 --> 00:44:17,865
But the rest of it, she needs work.

718
00:44:17,948 --> 00:44:18,949
How many catchphrases have there been?

719
00:44:19,033 --> 00:44:19,992
A lot.

720
00:44:21,744 --> 00:44:23,579
Yep. Jumped the gun.

721
00:44:23,662 --> 00:44:24,997
Hang on, he moves through shadows

722
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:26,290
and he's going to the Shadow Realm,

723
00:44:26,373 --> 00:44:27,374
it seems like that's where

724
00:44:27,458 --> 00:44:28,417
he's going to be the most powerful.

725
00:44:28,500 --> 00:44:29,543
You're right. We can't just go

726
00:44:29,626 --> 00:44:30,669
marching in there. It could be a trap.

727
00:44:30,753 --> 00:44:31,795
We'd be endangering the children.

728
00:44:31,879 --> 00:44:33,088
- Mm.
- We need reinforcements.

729
00:44:33,172 --> 00:44:34,173
We must raise an army.

730
00:44:34,256 --> 00:44:35,549
Are you thinking
what I think you're thinking?

731
00:44:35,632 --> 00:44:36,967
- I'm thinking it.
- What are we thinking?

732
00:44:37,051 --> 00:44:38,385
- Thinking what?
- I'm thinking it too.

733
00:44:38,469 --> 00:44:40,763
- Omnipotence City.
- Hmm!

734
00:44:40,846 --> 00:44:42,681
What's Omnipotence City?

735
00:44:42,765 --> 00:44:44,892
It's the home of the most
powerful gods in the universe.

736
00:44:45,059 --> 00:44:46,894
We could pull together
the greatest team ever.

737
00:44:47,061 --> 00:44:49,229
We could recruit Ra, Hercules,

738
00:44:49,313 --> 00:44:50,606
Tumatauenga

739
00:44:50,689 --> 00:44:52,107
Quetzalcoatl, maybe.

740
00:44:52,191 --> 00:44:54,443
And Zeus, the oldest
and wisest of them all.

741
00:44:54,526 --> 00:44:56,528
- Did you say Zeus?
- Yeah, Zeus.

742
00:44:56,612 --> 00:44:58,238
Like, the Zeus. Zeus-Zeus?

743
00:44:58,322 --> 00:44:59,656
I'm not sure if he has a second name.

744
00:44:59,740 --> 00:45:00,949
Do you think my god will be there,

745
00:45:01,033 --> 00:45:02,034
Ninny of the Nonny?

746
00:45:02,117 --> 00:45:03,118
Oh, you never know, Korg.

747
00:45:03,202 --> 00:45:04,161
But if they are,
we'll ask them to join our team.

748
00:45:04,244 --> 00:45:05,287
Yes.

749
00:45:05,371 --> 00:45:07,122
Stormbreaker.

750
00:45:07,206 --> 00:45:08,999
All right. Calm down. Relax.

751
00:45:09,083 --> 00:45:10,376
No, no, no, mate, we are not travelling

752
00:45:10,459 --> 00:45:12,002
in Stormbreaker's janky Bifrost.

753
00:45:12,086 --> 00:45:13,087
Look what just happened.

754
00:45:13,170 --> 00:45:14,671
We can't exactly go
in your tiny, little,

755
00:45:14,755 --> 00:45:16,465
flying portal horse, can we?
We won't all fit.

756
00:45:16,548 --> 00:45:18,050
What are you talking about?
Warsong's awesome.

757
00:45:18,133 --> 00:45:19,343
Stormbreaker's awesome too.

758
00:45:19,426 --> 00:45:20,803
Stormbreaker just needs a conduit.

759
00:45:20,886 --> 00:45:22,221
Anything that can handle space travel.

760
00:45:22,304 --> 00:45:23,639
I love it when she talks shop.

761
00:45:23,722 --> 00:45:25,140
It has the power to get us there,

762
00:45:25,224 --> 00:45:26,683
it just needs something
to focus that energy

763
00:45:26,767 --> 00:45:28,852
so it's not so unpredictable.

764
00:45:28,936 --> 00:45:30,896
You know, if we had a ship,
we could harness it

765
00:45:30,979 --> 00:45:32,564
and use Stormbreaker as a power source.

766
00:45:32,648 --> 00:45:34,483
- Oh, like an engine.
- Like an engine.

767
00:45:34,566 --> 00:45:35,692
You need a ship?

768
00:45:35,776 --> 00:45:36,944
I've got a ship.

769
00:45:41,865 --> 00:45:43,117
Get rid of all those seats.

770
00:45:43,283 --> 00:45:45,327
And you guys,
go tie those goats to the front.

771
00:45:45,494 --> 00:45:46,829
We leave in 15 minutes.

772
00:45:46,912 --> 00:45:48,831
Essentials only, everyone.

773
00:45:48,914 --> 00:45:50,791
That's essential. Mm-hmm.

774
00:45:50,874 --> 00:45:52,126
Fifteen minutes to departure!

775
00:45:52,209 --> 00:45:54,503
Well, you moved on quick,
didn't you?

776
00:45:55,671 --> 00:45:57,089
You're some piece of work.

